<br>
So, what I'm pondering is actually two things...would giving the pet one of those 2p vampire stakes allow the pet to hit this guy and also, exactly how does bane damage work.  Does it add to the dmg that the pet does?  If so, it doesn't show it in the melee window.  Also, since those stakes have a dmg of 2 or so, would the pet still do his max dmg? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 3:41:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: vampire in need of arse whoopin</span><hr size=1> Some guildmates went to the fort a while ago to kill vampires for fun and loot. Group avarage level wasn't all that high, about lv 51 and included al ranger lv 46 (aahhh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). I think we were 8 or nine in all and i think i was the highest there at lv 55. It was one of those guild groups where you are bored and grab the people that were at an appropiate level with no big regard to classes. I don't think we had an enchanter. We proceeded thru the fort, killing the vampires we met. We found that Heratius Golden was up. We had a diskussion on how to tackle him and ended up using my pet to disarm the HT. A lv 53 air pet lost 2/3 of its hp. After that he was not that big a problem. <br>
<br>
HOWEVER, Valdanov Zevfeer pops when Heraltius dies. He pops on the balcony, so he doesn't aggro. We did have a bunch of vampire bane weapons, including the cheap ones you can buy in Katta, which the pets were equipped with. Biggest problem was that he has a 1000 hp life tap, which makes him almost involnable and it was only when he eventually went oom that we started to make a dent in him. When he was at 80% health, only the wizard and I was still standing, I was oom, and the wizard evaced.<br>
<br>
Malosi had landed in first try.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, he needs to be stunned big time, possibly mana drained. One good tank (lv 55 or higher), two clerics and damage dealers like magicians or wizards are needed.<br>
<br>
Can you deal with the life tap, he is not a big problem.<br>
<br>
nmee <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
