<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=talusini>Talusini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 279<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/03 12:48:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/talusar/Face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: upper tower</span><hr size=1> I've confronted Zevfeer with my pet wielding the 2 vamp bane torches.  I was duoing with a cleric at the time.  Bad idea.  He has a 1500pt dmg proc or something like that.  You'd need at least a group to take him and SLOW would be MORE than a blessing.  He hits hard and fast.  He's level 62 I believe. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=411018&amp;resize=true&quot;" target="_new">Talusini Petuccini</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Mage - Master of the Elements<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swagman@themagicianstower>swagman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(2/16/03 12:37:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   cloak</span><hr size=1> im really just interest in soloing the named that drops the cloak. I saw a 62 mage do it, but i have been having problems with the named and a couple generals adding on me at tops stairs. I was just wondering how that mage got up there?<br>
<br>
its a nice camp btw the exp sucks but from selling gems and cotorie stuff and the bazaar u can make 600 pp on hour. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=talusini>Talusini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 281<br> <font color=#333333>(2/16/03 4:14:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/talusar/Face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: cloak</span><hr size=1> I've done the camp solo hundreds of times now.  It was VERY fun but very frustrating learning how to do it because of pet and mob poofing.  I was doing the camp for the cloak but NEVER got it.  I eventually had to buy it.  Got all sorts of the other rare drops including a few copies of levitate, everlasting breath, and spirit of flame.<br>
<br>
The trick is to use your Eye of Zomm to watch the named mob's pathing and use your pet to pull.  Target the mob with Eye of Zomm and wait til the named has moved on, then send pet in to attack and once pet has aggro, /pet back off and the mob will come to you (hint: pull from the stairs). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=411018&amp;resize=true&quot;" target="_new">Talusini Petuccini</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Mage - Master of the Elements<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silverrainmage>Silverrain mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 3:53:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: cloak</span><hr size=1> Farming vampire tower is easy, if you have your 61 air pet. I normally clear the tower in 30 to 45 min, depends on mind buffs. <br>
<br>
The trick is: clearing to tower from top down to bottom. Go as high as you can on the wall near the balcony. Cast levitate, cast pet, cast resist shield, drink sow potion (I have bard horsie). <br>
Two mobs are always up, now wait for named. Let named walk away for a few seconds, so he won’t join the fight. Now run to balcony. If you unable to catch it try again and look up in the sky, this should help.  <br>
<br>
General rule: always clear all mobs of the floor before you head down. Watch your pet, the pathing is weird. Be sure your pet is with you, before you start pulling. Have Summon companion ready and always have see invis up.<br>
<br>
Silverrain<br>
Arch Convoker<br>
Lanys T´Vyl <br>
<br>
P.S. I have an lvl 1 gnome necro in the tower. He is great for doing a camp check and dragging corpse, if needed.<br>
